Class MazeGenerator

java.lang.Object
fr.connexe.algo.generation.MazeGenerator
public class MazeGenerator extends Object

Generates mazes (perfect and not perfect) using various algorithms.

Every function of this class returns a MazeGenResult, which contains:

  • the generated maze, using GraphMaze
  • the complete generation log, using MazeGenLog

They also accept a seed for generating random numbers, which can be set to null to use a random seed.

    • introduceChaos

      public static void introduceChaos(MazeGenResult result, float probability, Long seed)

      Transforms a perfect maze into a non-perfect maze by randomly introducing chaos: some walls will appear, and some will be removed, randomly.

      The resulting maze is guaranteed to be non-perfect.

      Parameters:
      result - the result from a previous generation, which will be modified with chaos!
      probability - the probability of a wall being removed (0.0 to 1.0); will automatically be increased if it's too small for the given maze.
      seed - an optional seed for the RNG; a null value will generate a seed randomly.
